15/11/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR and the UNDP launched a conventional munitions disposal course Friday (12 November) for members of the BiH armed forces. 
The training, conducted at a SFOR base near Tuzla, is aimed at strengthening the military's capacity in implementing future demolition activities. 
The course is to be followed by safety and infrastructure upgrades of demolition ranges supported by the UNDP. 
According to the latest data, the ammunition surplus for the BiH armed forces has reached 33,500 tonnes. 
Experts say at least 10,000 tonnes ought to be destroyed immediately, in order to reduce hazards. 
(UNDP BiH Web site - 12/11/04)
